Package com.energyxxer.commodore.types

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CustomTypeInstantiator  
    TypeInstantiator<T extends Type>  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Type
    Defines a type of a Minecraft object of a certain category.
    Such categories are, by default, blocks, items, fluids, entities, biomes, difficulties, dimensions, status effects, enchantments, gamemodes, gamerules, item slots, particles, structures, functions and bossbars.
    TypeAssert
    Utility class whose purpose is to aid commands to validate types passed as parameters.
    As the standard is to never use Type subclasses to narrow down possible types, and instead compare types via their Type.category value, this class' methods do just that, throwing an exception if a type is not of a desired type.
    TypeDictionary
    Class which contains all the types of a specific category in a certain namespace.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    IllegalTypeException  
    TypeNotFoundException
